#dd bs=4M if=/home/sana/Downloads/ubuntu-18.04.2-live-server-amd64.iso of=/dev/sdb1 status=progress oflag=sync

From <https://vitux.com/how-to-create-a-bootable-usb-stick-from-the-ubuntu-terminal/> 


To format USB first unmount /dev/sdX

For partitioning :

Fdsik /dev/sdX

To delete partitions:
Type "d"
To create new partitions:
Type "n"
To write partitions:
W

# mkfs.ntfs /dev/sdXn

From <https://tecadmin.net/format-usb-in-linux/>